==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shim
<hw>Shim</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A kind of
shallow plow used in tillage to break the ground, and clear it of
weeds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>A thin piece of metal placed
between two parts to make a fit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shimmer</ent>⟦br⟧
